6. Clarifications About the Hosted-Service Restriction

For clarity:

(a) A customer may use Harmonia internally in its own environment, including on its own cloud accounts or machines.

(b) A consultant, integrator, contractor, or service provider may set up, customize, support, or operate Harmonia for a customer in that customer's own environment for the customer's internal use.

(c) You may use Harmonia internally to provide outputs or services to clients, provided the clients are not being sold hosted access to Harmonia itself.

(d) A service is treated as a prohibited hosted or managed service when a third party is effectively receiving Harmonia itself as an online service, rather than merely receiving results, deliverables, or professional services produced with the help of Harmonia.

